# 3: Colorsets
#
# Colorsets can be used to configure the color of the various
# parts of fvwm such as window decor, menus, modules, etc.
#
# Colorset Convention
#
#   0 - Default
#   1 - Inactive Windows
#   2 - Active Window
#   3 - Inactive Windows Borders
#   4 - Active Windows Borders
#   5 - Menu - Inactive Item
#   6 - Menu - Active Item
#   7 - Menu - Grayed Item
#   8 - Menu - Title
#   9 - Reserved
#  10+ Modules
#      10 - Module Default
#      11 - Module Hilight
#      12 - Module ActiveButton (Mouse Hover)
#      13 - FvwmPager Active Page
#      14 - FvwmIconMan Iconified Button
###########
# blue #0060a0
# light blue 00b0ef
# green #a0ffa0
#
# Material UI
# https://material.io/design/color/#tools-for-picking-colors
# #FFEB3B yellow
# #FFD600 dark yellow
# #BF360C red E63946
# #0288D1 blue
# #01579B dark blue
# #9E9E9E gray
#
# text
# light f0f0f0
# dark 282828
#
Colorset 0  fg #282828, bg gray65, hi, sh, Plain, NoShape
Colorset 1  fg #282828, bg Azure3, hi, sh, Plain, NoShape
